HEADWORD: Hangman
<hw>Hang"man</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧ng"m⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Hangmen</plw> <pr>(-m⟦eit⟧n)</pr>.</plu> <def>One
who hangs another; esp., one who makes a business of hanging; a public
executioner; -- sometimes used as a term of reproach, without reference
to office.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

